ScudCloud is a non official open-source Linux (Debian, Ubuntu, 
Kubuntu, Mint, Arch) desktop client for Slack©.i

Slack© is a platform for team communication.

ScudCloud uses the QT library + Webkit to render the web version 
of Slack, but using the QWebkit-Native bridge to improve desktop 
integration with:

multiple teams support,
native system notifications,
count of unread direct mentions at launcher/sytray icon,
alert/wobbling on new messages,
channels quicklist (Unity only),
optional "Close to Tray".
